This chapter describe the process to install the applicative server based on previously retrieved, extracted and configured release binary.

These task are mandatory prior any applicative or bd installation.

They need to be executed on every server referenced in `[INSTALL_SERVER]`.

Applicative installation go through the following step : 

* Backup previous applicative instances
* Execute Release installation process
* Proceed to configuration changes if any
* Proceed to other changes if any
* Checkup successful install


**Important** : 

* All of them are mandatory and shall be executed in this order.
* When a step fail, the process shall stop until the correction is found.
* Once correction have been achieved, the process can continue by restarting from the stopped step.

<h2> Prerequisite
</h2>

On every server referenced in `[INSTALL_SERVER]`, ensure that the following requirement are fulfilled : 

* Release archive deployment and configuration have been properly fulfilled, as described in the previous chapter.


Note that all those pre-requisites (as well as the global ones) will be checked during the deployment process prior to any deployment operation. 
If prerequisites are not checked, then the installation process will be aborted.


<h2> Backup Process
</h2>

On every Prod S3 bucket, ensure S3 Backup based on Ops process.

<h2> Deployment Process Detail
</h2>

On every server referenced in `[INSTALL_SERVER]`, execute deployment script

Logged as user `${USER_NAME}`, the update script must be executed

```shell
$ cd /app/release/${RELEASE_NAME}
$ ./update.sh ${ENV}
```

The script must finish without any error.


